      <h2 id="faq-heading" class="type-h2 text-warm-black mb-10">Frequently asked questions</h2>

      <div class="divide-y divide-warm-black/10">

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Do I need to know how to code?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">No. You describe what you want in plain language. AgentQ's AI agents handle the architecture, frontend, backend, and database. When things get complex, our developers step in through Developer&nbsp;Assist.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What if I already started building on another platform?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Bring it. We can work with what you've started or help you start fresh&nbsp;&mdash; whichever gets you to launch&nbsp;faster.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Do I own the code?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Completely. Your code is clean, documented, and yours. Hand it to any developer. Move it to any hosting provider. No lock-in, no proprietary&nbsp;platforms.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What kind of apps can AgentQ build?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Customer portals, SaaS products, internal tools, marketplaces, booking systems, dashboards&nbsp;&mdash; any web application. If you can describe it, we can build&nbsp;it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>How is this different from other AI app builders?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Two things. First: production-ready output&nbsp;&mdash; dedicated databases, enterprise security, clean code. Not the shared infrastructure and toy databases other tools ship. Second: on-demand developer assistance built into every plan. AI builders leave you alone when things break. AgentQ&nbsp;doesn't.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What does Developer Assist actually include?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Architecture guidance, integration support (payment gateways, CRMs, third-party APIs), professional code review and optimization, and deployment assistance. Real engineers in your workflow&nbsp;&mdash; not a chatbot. Included in every&nbsp;plan.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>What happens when my business grows?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Your software scales with you. As your needs get more complex, Developer Assist tiers scale up too. Enterprise plans include solutions architects who help with requirement gathering and build from the ground&nbsp;up.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Why not just use ChatGPT, Cursor, or Claude Code?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">Those tools are powerful&nbsp;&mdash; for developers. They require you to understand code, debug errors, make architecture decisions, and handle deployment yourself. If you're not technical, you'll hit a wall fast. AgentQ is built for people who want to describe what they need and get working software back, with a real developer when they need&nbsp;one.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
            <span>Why not hire a freelancer?</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" aria-hidden="true"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p class="type-body text-warm-mid pb-2">A freelancer who can build production-grade software starts at $5,000 for an MVP and takes weeks. You manage them, review their work, and hope they stick around for fixes. AgentQ costs $200 a month, delivers in days, and the developer support is ongoing. When you need changes next month, the support is still&nbsp;there.</p>
